Class SoftwareComponent

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.crismaproject.SoftwareComponent

  • public class SoftwareComponent
extends java.lang.Object
    This catalogue item represents the description of a Software Component that has been selected, extended or implemented by the CRISMA Consortium to realise a certain Building Block.

    • Field Detail

      • buildingBlock

        public BuildingBlock buildingBlock
        A reference to the Building Block that is realised by this Software Component.

      • developmentContext

        public SoftwareComponent.SoftwareComponentDevelopmentContext developmentContext
        Defines the context of development activities of the Software Component in CRISMA.
        • New: The Software Component a result of the CRISMA project and has been implemented from scratch.
        • Extended: The Software Component is based on existing software which has been directly extended or adapted to suit the needs of CRISMA.
        • Used: The Software Component is entirely based on existing software, no changes to the source code of the existing software are necessary or planned.

      • backgroundOwner

        public java.lang.String backgroundOwner
        The Name of the owner of the background software, if the development context of the Software Component is Extended or Used.

      • owner

        public java.lang.String owner
        The name of the owner of the Software Component (foreground). If the development context of the Software Component is Used, this field is empty.

      • type

        public java.lang.String[] type
        Defines the (technical type) type of the Software Component. This is an open list. some types to chose from are:
        • Wirecloud Widget
        • Desktop Application
        • OGC Service
        • Integration Platform
        • JavaScript Framework
        • ...

      • developmentStatus

        public java.lang.String developmentStatus
        This field describes the development status of the Software Component, e.g. "early prototype", "preview version", "final release", "no release available yet", etc.

      • version

        public java.lang.String version
        This field describes the current version number of the Software Component, e.g. 1.0.

      • summary

        public java.lang.String summary
        This field contains a short description (summary) the Software Component. It consists of plaintext only and is maximum 3-5 lines long. The summary may automatically be extracted from the description.

      • description

        public java.lang.String description
        The long description of the Software Component. May include formatted text, bullet lists, pictures, etc. Additionally, the description should provide technical details on the usage of Software Component, e.g. Hardware Requirements, supported Operating Systems, requirements for the installation (database, etc.), and so on.

      • backgroundLicense

        public java.lang.String backgroundLicense
        The name of the license of the background software on which the Software Component is based. If the development context of the Software Component is New, this field is empty.

      • license

        public java.lang.String license
        The name of the license of the Software Component (foreground) under which it is distributed by the CRISMA Consortium. If the development context of the Software Component is Used, this field is empty.

      • developmentPlan

        public java.net.URL developmentPlan
        A link to the detailed Development Plan of the Software Component. These documents are currently hosted on the VTT workspace and are visible to registered users only.

      • backgroundSoftware

        public java.net.URL backgroundSoftware
        An optional link to a website that describes the background software of this Software Component. Only relevant if the development context of the Software Component is Extended or Used.

      • sourcecode

        public java.net.URL sourcecode
        If the Software Component is released under an open source license, a link to the public software repository, e.g. github, should be provided.

      • download

        public java.net.URL download
        If the Software Component can be distributed and or and installed independently of a complete CRISMA Application, a link to the binaries of the latest stable release can be provided.

      • demo

        public java.net.URL[] demo
        If there exist online demos of the software, e.g. youtube videos, a web application (wirecloud), link should be provided.

      • documentation

        public java.net.URL[] documentation
        If there exist additional online documentation (e.g. user's guide, installation guide, etc.) of the Software Components besides the Functional Building Block Descriptions and the Implementation Plans, links should be provided.
